The paper proposes a programming framework for complex event processing, which involves specifying rules for correlating different event streams, detecting absence of events, and aggregating over sliding windows. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the language in an event-driven fashion, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper provides a formal semantics for the proposed framework, which suggests that it may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
